en:
Strength is a measure of your physical power. It affects your melee damage and your ability to carry heavy items.

[ul]Melee Damage
Carry Capacity
Parry
Various Effects on Armor and Dual Wield
Ranged Weapons Range
Ranged Weapons Damage[/ul]

Dexterity is a measure of your hand-eye coordination and reflexes. It affects your ranged damage and your ability to dodge attacks.

[ul]Hit Precision
Critical Hit Chance
Melee Damage with Daggers
Crafting Quality
Parry
Ranged Weapons Attack Speed[/ul]

Agility is a measure of your speed and nimbleness. It affects your movement speed and your ability to dodge attacks.

[ul]Movement Speed
Attack Speed
Melee Damage
Parry
Dodge
Various Effects on Dual Wield[/ul]

Constitution is a measure of your health and stamina. It affects your maximum health and your ability to resist poison.

[ul]
Damage Reduction
Health Regeneration
Resistance to Diseases and Various Effects[/ul]

Perception is a measure of your senses and awareness. It affects your ranged damage and your ability to detect hidden objects.

[ul]Ranged Hit Precision
Gathering Success
Spellcasting Range
Critical Hit Chance
Critical Hit Damage
Ranged Weapons Damage[/ul]

Intelligence is a measure of your knowledge and reasoning. It affects your maximum mana and your ability to resist magic.

[ul]Element Points
Spellcasting Effects
Melee Damage[/ul]

Arcanum is a measure of your magical power. It affects your spell damage and your ability to resist magic.

[ul]Mana Capacity
Mana Regeneration
Magic Defense[/ul]
